org.sbml.jsbml.ext

Interface SBasePlugin

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.io.Serializable, javax.swing.tree.TreeNode, TreeNodeWithChangeSupport
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractFBCSBasePlugin, AbstractRenderPlugin, AbstractSBasePlugin, AbstractSpatialSBasePlugin, ArraysSBasePlugin, CompModelPlugin, CompSBasePlugin, CompSBMLDocumentPlugin, DistribSBasePlugin, DynCompartmentPlugin, DynEventPlugin, DynSBasePlugin, FBCModelPlugin, FBCReactionPlugin, FBCSpeciesPlugin, GroupsModelPlugin, LayoutModelPlugin, MultiCompartmentPlugin, MultiModelPlugin, MultiSimpleSpeciesReferencePlugin, MultiSpeciesPlugin, MultiSpeciesReferencePlugin, QualitativeModel, QualModelPlugin, RenderGraphicalObjectPlugin, RenderLayoutPlugin, RenderListOfLayoutsPlugin, ReqSBasePlugin, SpatialCompartmentPlugin, SpatialModelPlugin, SpatialParameterPlugin, SpatialReactionPlugin, SpatialSpeciesPlugin

    public interface SBasePlugin
extends TreeNodeWithChangeSupport
    Defines the methods necessary for an SBase Plugin. When an SBML level 3 package is extending one of the core SBML elements with additional attributes or child elements, an SBasePlugin is created to serve as a place holder for these new attributes or elements.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Nicolas Rodriguez
